						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="italic">Gōpura</hi> of the same temple, right of entrance.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is incomplete. It is written in Grantha and Tamil characters.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Dēvarāya II (?): C. 15th century.</hi></p>						

						<p>It contains a part of the <hi rend="italic">praśasti</hi> usually found in the records of the Vijayanagara period. Among the <hi rend="italic">birudas</hi> are <hi rend="italic">Emmaṇḍalamum tiṟaikoṇḍa, Īḻam tiṟaikoṇḍa,</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Kesavēṭṭai-koṇḍaruḷiya.</hi></p>						

